engineDB::escape()

Description
    public string engineDB::escape(string $string)
    Escapes special characters in $string for use in a SQL statement.

Parameters
    string
	The string that is to be escaped.

Return Values
    Returns special character escaped string value.

Examples
    <?php
	...
	$sql = sprintf("INSERT INTO %s (name) VALUES('%s')",
	    $engine->openDB->escape($table),
	    $engine->cleanPost['MYSQL']['newListItem']
	    );

	$engine->openDB->sanitize = FALSE;
	$sqlResult = $engine->openDB->query($sql);
	...
    ?>

See Also
    engineDB::testConnection()
